<subSubSection id="1FC1D086FFB7FFA1FF5DFD61FC79DFEF" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="5764830DFFB7FFA1FF5DFD61FC79DFEF" blockId="40.[175,1005,194,977]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis id="65AF5F1FFFB7FFA1FF5DFD61FEDEDEC7" bold="true" box="[199,295,739,761]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is known from only 
<specimenCount id="41DD4884FFB7FFA1FDE4FD61FCF0DEC7" box="[638,777,739,761]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" type="generic">one specimen</specimenCount>
, the 
<typeStatus id="88603DAFFFB7FFA1FCA0FD61FC6EDEC7" box="[826,919,739,761]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">holotype</typeStatus>
. Having only 
<specimenCount id="41DD4884FFB7FFA1FF7EFD7CFE94DF2A" box="[228,365,766,788]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" type="generic">one specimen</specimenCount>
prevented preparation of a slide mount and measurements of ventral characters. 
<taxonomicName id="90DBF88EFFB7FFA1FEEBFC9BFD96DF10" authorityName="Hartley, Andrews &amp; McHugh" authorityYear="2008" box="[369,623,793,814]" class="Insecta" family="Latridiidae" genus="Akalyptoischion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pogonias">
<emphasis id="65AF5F1FFFB7FFA1FEEBFC9BFD96DF10" box="[369,623,793,814]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Akalyptoischion pogonias</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName id="90DBF88EFFB7FFA1FD44FC9BFCBBDF10" box="[734,834,793,814]" class="Insecta" family="Latridiidae" genus="Akalyptoischion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tomeus">
<emphasis id="65AF5F1FFFB7FFA1FD44FC9BFCBBDF10" box="[734,834,793,814]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">A. tomeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
superficially but can be recognized by the stout, erect setae present at the posterior corners and along the lateral margin of the head, the larger head foveae and the different pronotal foveae. 
<taxonomicName id="90DBF88EFFB7FFA1FEC7FCE8FDA5DF41" authorityName="Hartley, Andrews &amp; McHugh" authorityYear="2008" box="[349,604,874,895]" class="Insecta" family="Latridiidae" genus="Akalyptoischion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pogonias">
<emphasis id="65AF5F1FFFB7FFA1FEC7FCE8FDA5DF41" box="[349,604,874,895]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Akalyptoischion pogonias</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also may be confused with 
<taxonomicName id="90DBF88EFFB7FFA1FCE2FCE8FC14DF41" authorityName="Andrews" authorityYear="1976" box="[888,1005,874,895]" class="Insecta" family="Latridiidae" genus="Akalyptoischion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anasillos">
<emphasis id="65AF5F1FFFB7FFA1FCE2FCE8FC14DF41" box="[888,1005,874,895]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">A. anasillos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="90DBF88EFFB7FFA1FF45FC07FE74DFA4" authorityName="Hartley, Andrews &amp; McHugh" authorityYear="2008" box="[223,397,901,922]" class="Insecta" family="Latridiidae" genus="Akalyptoischion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hadromorphus">
<emphasis id="65AF5F1FFFB7FFA1FF45FC07FE74DFA4" box="[223,397,901,922]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">A. hadromorphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It may be distinguished from these species by its lack of punctation on the median surface of abdominal ventrite I, its large mandibles that are visible dorsally and the sparse setation of its head and pronotum.
</paragraph>
